This paper deals with the analysis of distance distributions in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the application of this analysis to various network characteristics such as energy consumption, interference, outage, and connectivity, which are areas of interest in information theory (cs.IT), mathematical analysis (cs.MA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents a model for the nodal arrangement in the network, which involves the use of probability distributions, making it relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
